Reasoning: The paper describes a metric for measuring the success of a complex system composed of agents performing autonomous behaviours. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, as it deals with the modelling and evaluation of intelligent agents. The paper also mentions the use of behavioural ontologies and decision making, which are common topics in Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the simulation evaluation of the system, which is a common topic in Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the capability for including rules or decision making into the script, which is a common topic in Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
